- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with detecting repetitions in a string, which can be seen as a form of compression or encoding. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the properties of strings and their repetitions. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve geometric concepts in the analysis of the algorithms.
